    <!--Class feats-->
    <Feat>
      <Name>Mage Hand - Bluff</Name>
      <Description>Allows you to attempt to bluff a target with your Mage Hand with an enhanced duration.
Bluffed enemies become more vulnerable to sneak attacks and your attacks produce
less hate for it's duration. While stealthed you can bluff enemies to walk away
from their friends.
Cooldown: 15 seconds
Duration: 8 seconds.</Description>
      <Acquire>Automatic</Acquire>
      <Icon>MageHandBluff</Icon>
    </Feat>
    <Feat>
      <Name>Mage Hand - Disable Traps</Name>
      <Description>Allows you to attempt to disarm traps at a distance using your Mage Hand.</Description>
      <Acquire>Automatic</Acquire>
      <Icon>MageHandDisableTraps</Icon>
    </Feat>
    <Feat>
      <Name>Magical Ambush</Name>
      <Description>Your offensive instantaneous damaging spells deal additional 1d6 force damage
equal to your sneak attack dice. Scales with 50% of force spell power.
This proc has no cool down so it works very well with multi missile spells
like magic missile. The sneak dice will not function on DOTS, Pale Master
Aura, Wall of Fire, etc.</Description>
      <Acquire>Automatic</Acquire>
      <Icon>MagicalAmbush</Icon>
    </Feat>
    <Feat>
      <Name>Spell Thief</Name>
      <Description>Your melee and missile attacks that strike targets who have spells grant spell
points. 1d20 spell points on a 5 second cooldown for melee attacks.
Ranged is a 10 second cooldown.</Description>
      <Acquire>Automatic</Acquire>
      <Icon>SpellThief</Icon>
    </Feat>
    <Feat>
      <Name>Past Life: Rogue - Arcane Trickster</Name>
      <Description>You were an Arcane Trickster in a past life. You delight in illusions and have
a knack for applying physical force with magic. Each time you acquire this feat
you gain +3 Force Spell Power and a +1 bonus to Illusion DCs.
This feat can be stacked up to three times.</Description>
      <MaxTimesAcquire>3</MaxTimesAcquire>
      <Acquire>HeroicPastLife</Acquire>
      <Icon>PastLifeRogue</Icon>
      <Effect>
        <Type>SpellDC</Type>
        <Bonus>Feat</Bonus>
        <Item>Illusion</Item>
        <AType>Simple</AType>
        <Amount size="1">1</Amount>
      </Effect>
      <Effect>
